## PITFALLS

| Pitfall | Quick fix |
|---------|-----------|
| Reading entire bulletin files | Use `extract_tables` or `search_corpus` |
| Fiscal/calendar year confusion | FY ends Sept 30; calendar year ends Dec 31 |
| Wrong units (millions vs billions) | Always check the table header row |
| Rounding intermediate values | Only round the final result |
| Stopping at first plausible answer | Use `find_latest_value` — bulletins revise prior figures |
| ESF "Capital account" ≠ total capital | ESF capital = sum of all capital lines; check ALL rows |
| `%` sign | Only include if question explicitly uses it |
| Missing unit suffix | Re-read question: "Report in millions" → write `36080 million` not `36080` |
| Missing text verdict | `[0.012]` wrong when question asks surplus/deficit → `[0.012, surplus]` |
| Dropped `$` sign | When question/table uses dollars → `$37,921,314` not `37921314` |
| Comma stripping | Preserve `2,602` from corpus; bracket lists: `[374,443, 381,327]` |
| Multiple tables same bulletin | Read header of EACH match — different tables cover different date ranges |
| Chart/visual question | Search for underlying tabular data (±50 lines of exhibit ref) before guessing |

